# Hubly brand logo

The official Hubly logo is the lowercase wordmark **hub** + **ly**:

- **hub** — dark navy (`#141B2B`)
- **ly** — bright orange (`#D9632D`)
- Font feel: clean, modern, rounded sans (matches Plus Jakarta Sans / DM Sans weight 700–800)

## Asset files

- Light backgrounds: `assets/hubly-wordmark.png` (also `public/assets/hubly-wordmark.png`)
- Dark backgrounds: `assets/hubly-wordmark-on-dark.png` (white hub + orange ly)

## Rules

1. Whenever Hubly appears as a **logo / brand mark** (nav, hero, auth, boot, footer, coach chrome, empty states), use the wordmark image — not plain unstyled text "hubly".
2. Prefer `<img class="hubly-mark" src="assets/hubly-wordmark.png" alt="hubly">` (or `-on-dark` on dark UI).
3. In body copy (“Hubly builds…”, “Hubly Coach”), capitalized Hubly is fine as text; when the coach header or FAB branding shows, still use the mark.
4. Do not invent a different logo treatment (all-orange, emoji, icon-only, title case HubLy, etc.).
5. Brand accent CTAs should stay in the logo orange family (`#D9632D` / `--brand`).
